cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.HC

This paper presents a method for detecting and modeling cycles in multidimensional time series data, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with missing data and can cluster individual time series into groups, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
